        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 6:02PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 601 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Echo, or 7 miles northeast of Coleman, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Coleman, Cross Plains, Byrds, Grosvenor, Lake Brownwood State Park,
Burkett, May, Cross Cut, Echo, Us-283 Near The Coleman-
Callahan County Line, and Lake Coleman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
